{"parse":{"title":"Dowager","pageid":338096,"revid":854294379,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>dowager</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Widow\" title=\"Widow\">widow</a> who holds a title or property\u2014a \"<a href=\"/wiki/Dower\" title=\"Dower\">dower</a>\"\u2014derived from her deceased husband.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> As an adjective, <i>dowager</i> usually appears in association with <a href=\"/wiki/Monarchy\" title=\"Monarchy\">monarchical</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Aristocracy\" title=\"Aristocracy\">aristocratic</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Title#Aristocratic_titles\" title=\"Title\">titles</a>.\n</p><p>In popular usage, the noun <i>dowager</i> may refer to any elderly widow, especially one of both wealth and dignity.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Use\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Use</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#In_the_United_Kingdom\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In the United Kingdom</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#In_other_countries\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In other countries</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Use\">Use</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dowager&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Use\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg/220px-Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"173\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg/330px-Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg/440px-Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1280\" data-file-height=\"1007\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Louis_XIV_of_France_and_his_family_attributed_to_Nicolas_de_Largilli%C3%A8re.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/wiki/Madame_de_Ventadour\" title=\"Madame de Ventadour\">Dowager Duchess of Ventadour</a> in full mourning attends the King of France.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg/220px-L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"215\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg/330px-L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg/440px-L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"835\" data-file-height=\"816\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:L%27imp%C3%A9ratrice_Eug%C3%A9nie_en_deuil_1873.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The dowager Empress of France in <i>Grand Deuil</i></div></div></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_the_United_Kingdom\">In the United Kingdom</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dowager&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: In the United Kingdom\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">United Kingdom</a>, the widow of a <a href=\"/wiki/Peerage\" title=\"Peerage\">peer</a> may continue to use the style she had during her husband's lifetime, e.g. \"<a href=\"/wiki/Count\" title=\"Count\">Countess</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Placeholder_name\" title=\"Placeholder name\">Loamshire</a>\", provided that his successor, if any, has no wife to bear the plain title.  Otherwise she more properly prefixes either her <a href=\"/wiki/Given_name\" title=\"Given name\">forename</a> or the word <i>Dowager</i>, e.g. \"Jane, Countess of Loamshire\" or \"Dowager Countess of Loamshire\" (In any case she would continue to be called \"Lady Loamshire\").\n</p><p>The term <i><a href=\"/wiki/Queen_dowager\" title=\"Queen dowager\">queen dowager</a></i> is used in the United Kingdom and several other countries for the widow of a king.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_other_countries\">In other countries</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dowager&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: In other countries\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>This form of address used for noble ladies whose husbands have died. It was used for the late <a href=\"/wiki/Fabiola_of_Belgium\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fabiola of Belgium\">Queen Dowager, Fabiola</a> of Belgium and for the <a href=\"/wiki/Anna_Maria_Komorowska\" title=\"Anna Maria Komorowska\">Dowager countess d'Udekem d'Acoz</a>. \n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Queen_Victoria_Eugenia_of_Spain\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen Victoria Eugenia of Spain\">Queen Victoria Eugenia of Spain</a> was known as dowager queen after the death of her husband.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dowager&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://womenshistory.about.com/od/marriageoverview/a/dowager.htm\">\"Queen as a Title - History of Titles for Female Rulers\"</a>. <i>about.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">19 March</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=about.com&amp;rft.atitle=Queen+as+a+Title+-+History+of+Titles+for+Female+Rulers&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwomenshistory.about.com%2Fod%2Fmarriageoverview%2Fa%2Fdowager.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADowager\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">lesoir.be. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lesoir.be/1286062/article/soirmag/soirmag-histoire/2016-08-08/baudouin-et-fabiola-un-couple-fusionnel\">\"Baudouin et Fabiola, un couple fusionnel\"</a>. <i>lesoir.be</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">19 March</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=lesoir.be&amp;rft.atitle=Baudouin+et+Fabiola%2C+un+couple+fusionnel&amp;rft.au=lesoir.be&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lesoir.be%2F1286062%2Farticle%2Fsoirmag%2Fsoirmag-histoire%2F2016-08-08%2Fbaudouin-et-fabiola-un-couple-fusionnel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADowager\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dowager&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/40px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//u